                cwd/examples/molecules/He/he_simple_opt.xml → real file, B=0.810000 (perturbed deep path)
    Mechanism: validation/veloc/runner.py:_symlink_input_data materializes TWO views of the
    input — basename at cwd top-level (for `-in <basename>` invocations launched from cwd)
    AND the deep input_subdir mirror. apply_perturbation only rewrote the deep path because
    PerturbationSpec.file is declared in YAML as the deep path (e.g. "examples/free/in.validation").
    The binary's command line reads cwd/<basename> (top-level symlink → unperturbed source).
    Perturbation is a silent no-op for any app with input_subdir set.
  affected apps: SPARTA, SPPARKS, QMCPACK, HyPar (only the 4 with input_subdir + perturbation.file
    starting with input_subdir).
  fix applied (validation/veloc/app_config.py:247-269): after writing perturbed content to the
    deep path, also rewrite cwd/<basename> IFF that path is a symlink whose resolved target
    equals the source we just read from. Conservative: never clobbers an unrelated file with
    the same basename, never overwrites a symlink pointing somewhere else.
  regression tests (tests/test_perturbation.py:369-487):
    - test_regex_replace_writes_top_level_alias_when_input_subdir (pins the bug-fix behavior)
    - test_regex_replace_top_level_alias_unrelated_file_preserved (safety: real file unchanged)
    - test_regex_replace_top_level_alias_other_symlink_target_preserved (safety: other symlink unchanged)
  consumer-side note: the same apply_perturbation is invoked by both calibrator
    (perturbation_calibrator.py:calibrate) AND runtime validator
    (validate.py:_run_perturbation_for_recovery and runner.py per-leg invocations). The bug
    therefore corrupted BOTH calibration verdicts AND runtime gating for any input_subdir app —
    runtime perturbation_active=True was being reported in proof.json while the binary actually
    ran on unperturbed input. HyPar's pre-fix TRUSTED verdict is therefore suspect even though
