PART 2 -- ROOT CAUSE: validator perturbation-overlay leaves cwd-root
input-file alias stale, so the binary reads OLD perturbation value
while validator THINKS it perturbed to a new value.
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Empirical state of resilient_clean/ directories (as of audit time):

  HyPar (last validation: 2026-05-21 20:39 -- BEFORE fix commit
         44c737672 at 2026-05-21 23:50):
    cwd/physics.inp                                = SYMLINK -> source
                                                     unperturbed (mtime
                                                     2026-05-20 21:57)
    cwd/Examples/1D/FPDoubleWell/physics.inp        = REAL FILE perturbed
                                                     (q=0.241859, mtime
                                                     2026-05-21 20:39)
    -> binary calls fopen("physics.inp") in cwd -> reads VANILLA q=0.24
    -> output bit-identical to baseline_cache (which is unperturbed)
    -> != Z_P (perturbed-vanilla q=0.241859) -> Test 2 FAIL ("real
       regression" appears).  Cause: top-level alias fix from commit
       44c737672 did not yet exist when this validation ran.

  SPPARKS (last validation: 2026-05-23 01:39 -- AFTER fix commit):
    cwd/in.validation                          = REAL FILE seed=693161351
                                                 (mtime 2026-05-23 01:21
                                                 = FIRST cycle this
                                                 session, when fix
                                                 promoted alias)
    cwd/examples/ising/in.validation           = REAL FILE seed=402480231
                                                 (mtime 2026-05-23 01:39
                                                 = SECOND cycle, 18 min
                                                 later)
    proof.json perturbation_value             = 402480231 (matches deep
                                                 file, not cwd-root)
    -> binary runs with -in in.validation -> reads STALE seed=693161351
    -> Z_P collected with seed=402480231 -> outputs diverge -> Test 2 FAIL
    -> output_correct = False  in proof.json

  SPARTA (last validation: 2026-05-23 02:36 -- AFTER fix commit):
    cwd/in.validation                          = REAL FILE seed=667033
                                                 (mtime 2026-05-23 02:20)
    cwd/examples/free/in.validation            = REAL FILE seed=938525
                                                 (mtime 2026-05-23 02:36)
    -> same mechanism as SPPARKS.

THE BUG (validation/veloc/app_config.py:264-272, commit 44c737672):

    top_level_alias = cwd / Path(spec.file).name
    if top_level_alias != target_in_cwd and top_level_alias.is_symlink():
        try:
            alias_matches = top_level_alias.resolve() == source_path.resolve()
        except OSError:
            alias_matches = False
        if alias_matches:
            top_level_alias.unlink()
            top_level_alias.write_text(new_content)

  The `is_symlink()` guard is correct for the FIRST perturbation cycle in
  a fresh resilient_clean/ dir (alias was just created by
  _symlink_input_data).  But on the SECOND cycle, the alias is no longer
  a symlink -- it is the real file written by the FIRST cycle's
  unlink()+write_text().  The guard returns False; the alias is left
  stale; the deep target_in_cwd is rewritten with the new value; the
  binary reads the stale alias.

  This explains BOTH the HyPar case (fix didn't exist on May 21) AND the
  SPPARKS/SPARTA case (fix exists but doesn't handle subsequent-cycle
  state).

PROPOSED FIX (in validation/veloc/app_config.py, replacing lines 254-272):
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

    # Top-level alias write: _symlink_input_data may have placed a
    # symlink at cwd/<basename> pointing at the same source the binary
    # actually opens (e.g. `mpirun ... -in in.validation` from cwd).
    # Without refreshing, perturbations whose spec.file lives under
    # input_subdir land at the deep path and the binary keeps reading
    # the unperturbed (first cycle) or STALE (subsequent cycles)
    # top-level file.  Originally added 2026-05-21 with an is_symlink()
    # guard; extended 2026-05-23 to handle subsequent-cycle state
    # after the first apply_perturbation has promoted the alias to a
    # real file.  Safety: when the alias is already a real file, only
    # overwrite when its content matches the perturbation regex (so an
    # unrelated file with a colliding basename is never clobbered).
    top_level_alias = cwd / Path(spec.file).name
    if top_level_alias != target_in_cwd:
        should_overwrite = False
        if top_level_alias.is_symlink():
            try:
                should_overwrite = (
                    top_level_alias.resolve() == source_path.resolve()
                )
            except OSError:
                should_overwrite = False
        elif top_level_alias.is_file():
            try:
                existing = top_level_alias.read_text()
                should_overwrite = bool(re.search(spec.pattern, existing))
            except (OSError, UnicodeDecodeError):
                should_overwrite = False
        if should_overwrite:
            if top_level_alias.is_symlink() or top_level_alias.exists():
                top_level_alias.unlink()
            top_level_alias.write_text(new_content)

