Context
-------
Three commits earlier today (HyPar BLOCKED 2026-05-21, SPPARKS UNTRUSTED 01:51,
SPARTA UNTRUSTED 02:42) were rendered against a faulty perturbation alias-refresh
in validation/veloc/app_config.py:264-272 (commit 44c737672, 2026-05-21).  This
session's prior diagnostic block on this _decisions.log already documents the
mechanism and the proposed fix.  This entry records that (a) the fix is now
landed in app_config.py, (b) the three trust verdicts are reverted to
PENDING_REVALIDATION, and (c) the bench-stage per-run output-correctness check
(designed earlier this session, 12 unit tests passing) is committed in the same
patch so future bench runs have per-run output verdicts.

Code changes landed
-------------------
1) validation/veloc/app_config.py
   Alias-refresh now handles BOTH the symlink case (first cycle) AND the real-
   file case (subsequent cycles).  When the alias is already a real file from
   a prior apply_perturbation(), it is overwritten ONLY when its content
   matches the perturbation regex (collision-safe: unrelated files with a
   colliding basename are never clobbered).  Existing safety tests for
   unrelated-real-file and different-symlink-target preservation continue to
   pass.

2) validation/veloc/validate.py + validation/veloc/metrics_collector.py
   New per-run output-correctness check in the BENCH stage.  Each bench run
   has its output compared to the canonical baseline at
   build/baseline_cache/<APP>/<output_file_name> using the same comparator
   the correctness stage uses.  Result is carried on RunMetrics
   (output_correct, output_compare_method, output_compare_message), round-
   tripped through bench progress JSON, and aggregated by _build_summary
   into a per-(scenario, codebase) all_passed boolean.  Opt-in: returns
   (None, None) when the baseline file is missing, so legacy apps without
   a cached baseline are unaffected.  Bench uses FIXED CANONICAL inputs
   (no perturbation) — perturbation is correctness-stage only, by user
   design rule (2026-05-23).  Output-correct never feeds back to the LLM
   in run_iterative.sh; it is a measurement, not a gate input.

3) tests/test_bench_correctness.py (NEW, 12 tests)
   Covers RunMetrics field plumbing, bench-progress round-trip,
   _build_summary aggregation (all-pass / any-fail / all-none / partial),
   and _build_bench_output_check closure (missing baseline → opt-out,
   passing on byte match, failing on byte mismatch, failing on missing
   candidate).

4) tests/test_perturbation.py
   Added test_regex_replace_top_level_alias_refreshed_on_subsequent_cycle
   regression test: explicitly exercises the SECOND-CYCLE state where the
   alias is already a real file (because cycle 1 promoted it via
   unlink()+write_text()) and must be refreshed to cycle 2's value.  Asserts
   "111111" no longer present after cycle 2 writes "222222".  All 131
   perturbation + bench-correctness tests pass.

