  core/rio/io-serialize.c — only pe->stats.s_rio_load referenced,
  and that's RIO's own internal timer).  Post-recovery stats restart
  from zero so the reduction missed the work done before the crash.

Schema change (vanilla + checkpointed mirror, byte-identical):
  v9.4: 2 doubles = MPI_SUM(pe->stats.s_net_events,
                              pe->stats.s_nsend_net_remote)
  v9.5: 4 doubles = MPI_SUM(lp->rng->Cg[j]) for j=0..3 across all
        4 MPI ranks x 4000 LPs/rank.
  RIO io-serialize.c:11-13 stores Cg/Lg/Ig, lines 37-39 restore.
  tw_rand_reverse_unif (rand-clcg4.c:460-483) reverses each draw on
  rollback, so committed-Cg should be reproducible across recovery.

