  root cause: opencode 1.4.0 dies ~1.5s into startup with SIGKILL when the slot's SQLite DB contains a stale (mid-stream / abandoned) session. The orchestrator wipes /tmp/opencode_worker_* only at startup (run_parallel_queue.py:123) — never between iters — so a slot's DB accumulates session state from the first iter that ran there. Iter_1 of SAMRAI ended rc=137 (the wrapper's EXIT trap pkill-9-P during process teardown) leaving its DB session abandoned; iter_2+ then crashes the relaunched opencode process.
